$interpreted: Maria: Master! Master Clark, look at this!
Clark: What is it?
Maria: This is "Gake"! Very sweet and very delicious "Gake"! Maria wants Master Clark to try some!
Clark: You mean "cake"...wait a sec. Can you eat human food? Plus, where'd you get the money?
Angry Man: There she is! I found her!
Shop Owner: That's her! She ate ten cakes and didn't pay a dime!
Stall-Keeper: And she knocked over my flower vase! Absolutely no manners!
Whining Boy: She stepped on my cat's tail...*sob*...*sob*...
Clark: Wait, wait, wait...you──
Clark: I'm so sorry. Here, take this money. From now on, I'll take good care of her and won't let her run around...
Shop Owner: Hmph! Next time she just helps herself like this is a gosh darned buffet, I'll hand her over to the authorities!
Maria: Master Clark! Where are those things going?
Clark: Those are little birds. I'm not sure where they are going.
Maria: Ah──they landed on top of that~what is that?
Clark: It's a house...
Maria: Then that behind it...ooh, and that, what's that!?
Clark: ...Maria, listen to me. You can't take things from people without paying for them.
Maria: Paying? What is this "paying" that you speak of?
Clark: When you take a cake that somebody else made, you must give them the requisite amount of compensation. That way it is fair.
Maria: Maria just wanted Master to try a piece, that's all...
Clark: So, you've got to pay money for it...
Maria: Can Master give Maria some money?
Clark: These last two days you've been running around and now all my money's gone. Haven't you noticed I've been trying to make money at this stand here?
Clark: You'd best head back to the motel...and don't go sneaking out again──
Clark: Maria? What's the matter?
Maria: Here. Maria is hurting here.
Clark: Your stomach? But you're a robot...
Clark: Ah! So you can't just eat whatever you'd like!
Maria: Maria feels not so good...Master...I...
Clark: Maria!
Clark: This shouldn't be a problem...
Clark: (Amazing. She can't eat human food, but she understands...but then again, why does she have such a strong olfactory sense?)
Clark: (What was her maker thinking? What on earth could her purpose be...?)
Clark: (Plus, she's got exceptional fighting skills...it seems I've picked up an extraordinary attendant)
Maria: Backup Main Core restart complete, confirming user. May I ask what the user's name is?
Clark: Maria, I'm Clark. Don't you remember?
Maria: Master Clark! Maria welcomes you again!
Clark: Eh? This time you have some memory?
Maria: Master Clark, please state the next command!
Clark: Command...uhh...umm...you can't eat human food.
Maria: Order received! Maria will comply!
Clark: This is a Rune Item I made myself.
Clark: I must take care of the stand. If you're bored staying in the motel room, you can play with it.
Maria: A small bird! A small bird!
Clark: You can choose a name for it.
Maria: Maria can choose its name?
Clark: Your name is Maria, my name is Clark...
Maria: So, Maria is the little bird's master?
Clark: Yes. From now on, you are its master. You have to take care of it, protect it...
Clark: Because you're its master...
